      },
      "explanation": "Efforts-standard phrases carry different obligation strengths in commercial drafting. *Bloor v. Falstaff* (2d Cir. 1979) and its progeny treat `best efforts` as the most demanding, `commercially reasonable efforts` as the middle term, and `reasonable efforts` as the weakest — but without an in-document definition, the parties can dispute which standard applies and what conduct satisfies it.",
